Date:11/6/2007 10:22:09 AM
From:MCsweet
MNDO,

MNDO pays a nice dividend while you are waiting and has a solid cash hoard.

Auction rate preferred securities for the most part are relatively safe
investments that provide slightly higher yields than money market instruments.
The auction rate preferred market has firmed up from a couple months ago, so
unless the companies preferreds are backed by some terrible assets I wouldn't
worry too much.

The auction rate preferreds I know of are backed by closed-end fund assets and
are a legitimate AAA in my view versus say a sham AAA rating backed by subprime
paper. For example, a fund's NAV would have to go to 0 before the preferred
lose money, and before that happens the fund is forced to redeem the preferred
when the NAV starts dropping.

I haven't heard the call, yet, but looking forward to.

Best,
MC
